CatDescriptText: Miss Donna Youngblood, 3386 Milwaukee Street., was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 16, 1958, pg. 3 with question: "Do you think that Negroes are giving sufficient financial help to the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People?"  Answer reads: "No, I don't think so. The people can give a lot more.  However, although the NAACP is for the betterment of the race, a lot of people seem as though they are not interested."
